<REFENTRY id="link">
<REFMETA><REFENTRYTITLE>
link
</REFENTRYTITLE></REFMETA>
<REFNAMEDIV>
<REFNAME>link</REFNAME>
<REFPURPOSE>
make a new name for a file
</REFPURPOSE>
</REFNAMEDIV>
<REFSECT1>
<TITLE>Note</TITLE>
<PARA>
While GNU fileutils doesn't provide "link", it does provide the "ln" command,
both of which create hard links to files.
</PARA>
</REFSECT1>
